# GitHub Issue & Project Management

## Context
- Applies when creating issues from task documents
- Applies when managing project roadmaps via GitHub CLI
- **Applies when creating Pull Requests**

## Rules

1. **Issue Creation**:
   - Source tasks from `tasks/priority-N/` markdown files.
   - Use `gh issue create` with title `[#NNN] Title`, body from file, and appropriate labels.
   - Labels must include:
     - Priority: `priority-N` (1-4)
     - Type: `feature`, `bugfix`, `refactoring`, `testing`
     - Layer: `API`, `Service`, `Repository`, `Event` (optional)
     - Component: `Auth`, `User`, `Analysis`, `Notification` (optional)

2. **Project & Roadmap**:
   - Use Project V2 Node IDs for item manipulation.
   - Required Fields: `Start Date` and `End Date` (Type: `DATE`).
   - Set dates via `gh project item-edit --project-id <NodeID>`.

3. **Pull Request Requirements**:
   - **Mandatory**: Build successful (Gradle), all tests passing.
   - **Code Quality**: Linter passing (Checkstyle/Spotless), no major SonarQube issues.
   - **Template**: Include description, related issue, API changes (if any), testing checklist.

4. **Automation**:
   - Verify field IDs via `gh project field-list` before editing.
   - Use batch scripts for multiple issue creation.

## Examples

<example>
# Create Backend issue with full labels
gh issue create \
  -t "[#001] Implement User Authentication API" \
  -F tasks/priority-1/001-auth-api.md \
  -l "priority-1,feature,API,Auth"

# Add to project and set roadmap dates
ITEM_ID=$(gh project item-add <PROJECT_ID> --url <issue-url> --format json | jq -r '.id')
gh project item-edit --id $ITEM_ID --project-id <NodeID> --field-id <StartFieldID> --date 2025-12-11
gh project item-edit --id $ITEM_ID --project-id <NodeID> --field-id <EndFieldID> --date 2025-12-25
</example>

<example>
# Create PR with Backend checklist
gh pr create \
  -t "Feat: Add JWT Authentication Filter" \
  -b "## Description
Implement JWT validation logic in Spring Security filter chain.

## Related Issue
Closes #001

## Testing
- [x] Unit tests for TokenProvider
- [x] Integration test for AuthController
- [x] Tested with Postman

## Checklist
- [x] Checkstyle passing
- [x] API Docs updated (Swagger)
- [x] No sensitive data logged"
</example>

## Backend PR Checklist Template
```markdown
- [ ] Build successful (Gradle build)
- [ ] Unit/Integration tests added and passing
- [ ] Code style checked (Checkstyle/Spotless)
- [ ] API Documentation updated (Swagger/OpenAPI)
- [ ] Database migrations tested (if applicable)
- [ ] Environment variables documented
```
